tags":[],"text":"mas pesada que un abanico de tablones\n","title":""},{"date":"2024-07-25","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/240725_keanu-reeves_company-is-a-choice/","summary":"Alguien me dijo el otro día que se sentía mal por los solteros porque se sienten solos\u0026hellip; No es cierto, que yo soy soltero y no me siento solo. Salgo a comer solo. Una vez que sabes cuidar de ti mismo la compañía se convierte en una opción y no en una necesidad.","tags":[],"text":"alguien me dijo el otro día que se sentía mal por los solteros porque se sienten solos\u0026hellip; no es cierto, que yo soy soltero y no me siento solo. salgo a comer solo. una vez que sabes cuidar de ti mismo la compañía se convierte en una opción y no en una necesidad.\n","title":""},{"date":"2024-02-03","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/240203_montaigne_creer-lo-desconocido/","summary":"Nada se cree tan firmemente como aquello que menos se conoce","tags":[],"text":"nada se cree tan firmemente como aquello que menos se conoce\n","title":""},{"date":"2023-09-30","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/230930_rob-walker_manera-interesante-estar-interesado/","summary":"La manera de ser interesante es estar interesado.","tags":[],"text":"la manera de ser interesante es estar interesado.\n","title":""},{"date":"2023-03-18","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/230318_sam-morril_babies-look-racist-skindheads/","summary":"Babies look racist, they are skindheads, they are not educated.","tags":[],"text":"babies look racist, they are skindheads, they are not educated.\n","title":""},{"date":"2021-12-25","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/211225_andersen_whats-plausible/","summary":"Anything is possible, but I’m interested in what’s plausible.","tags":[],"text":"anything is possible, but i’m interested in what’s plausible.\n","title":""},{"date":"2021-12-13","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/211213_naval-ravikant_for-profit-takes-reality-feedback/","summary":"If you want to change the world to a better place, the best way to do it is a for-profit because for-profits have to take feedback from reality. Ironically, for-profit entities are more sustainable than non-profit entities. They’re self-sustainable. You’re not out there with a begging bowl all the time. Of course, you lose the beautiful non-profit status; you have to pay your taxes; and also you can get corrupted by being purely for-profit. But I would argue that the best businesses are the ones that are for-profit, sustainable and ethical so you can attract the best people. You can sustain it because it’s a mission and it’s not just about the money—because there are diminishing returns to making money.","tags":[],"text":"if you want to change the world to a better place, the best way to do it is a for-profit because for-profits have to take feedback from reality. ironically, for-profit entities are more sustainable than non-profit entities. they’re self-sustainable. you’re not out there with a begging bowl all the time. of course, you lose the beautiful non-profit status; you have to pay your taxes; and also you can get corrupted by being purely for-profit. but i would argue that the best businesses are the ones that are for-profit, sustainable and ethical so you can attract the best people. you can sustain it because it’s a mission and it’s not just about the money—because there are diminishing returns to making money.\n","title":""},{"date":"2021-08-22","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/210822_charlie-munger_charlie-munger/","summary":"As long as I have a book in my hand, I don’t feel like I’m wasting time.","tags":[],"text":"as long as i have a book in my hand, i don’t feel like i’m wasting time.\n","title":""},{"date":"2017-11-18","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/171118_high-sparrow_im-special/","summary":"Well, I tell them no one\u0026rsquo;s special, and they think I\u0026rsquo;m special for telling them so.","tags":[],"text":"well, i tell them no one\u0026rsquo;s special, and they think i\u0026rsquo;m special for telling them so.\n","title":""},{"date":"2026-03-09","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/260309_max-schumacher_life-from-bugs-bunny/","summary":"I\u0026rsquo;m not sure she is capable of any real feelings. She is television generation. She learned life from Bugs Bunny. The only reality she knows comes to her over the TV set.","tags":[],"text":"i\u0026rsquo;m not sure she is capable of any real feelings. she is television generation. she learned life from bugs bunny. the only reality she knows comes to her over the tv set.\n","title":""},{"date":"2025-12-15","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/251215_freysa_die-for-the-right/","summary":"Dying for the right cause is the most human thing we can do.","tags":[],"text":"dying for the right cause is the most human thing we can do.\n","title":""},{"date":"2025-02-15","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/250215_ann-druyan_found-each-other-in/","summary":"Every single moment that we were alive and we were together was miraculous-not miraculous in the sense of inexplicable or supernatural. We knew we were beneficiaries of chance. . . . That pure chance could be so generous and so kind. . . . That we could find each other, as Carl wrote so beautifully in Cosmos, you know, in the vastness of space and the immensity of time. . . . That we could be together for twenty years. That is something which sustains me and it’s much more meaningful. . . . The way he treated me and the way I treated him, the way we took care of each other and our family, while he lived. That is so much more important than the idea I will see him someday. I don\u0026rsquo;t think I\u0026rsquo;ll ever see Carl again. But I saw him. We saw each other. We found each other in the cosmos, and that was wonderful.","tags":[],"text":"every single moment that we were alive and we were together was miraculous-not miraculous in the sense of inexplicable or supernatural. we knew we were beneficiaries of chance. . . . that pure chance could be so generous and so kind. . . . that we could find each other, as carl wrote so beautifully in cosmos, you know, in the vastness of space and the immensity of time. . . . that we could be together for twenty years. that is something which sustains me and it’s much more meaningful. . . . the way he treated me and the way i treated him, the way we took care of each other and our family, while he lived. that is so much more important than the idea i will see him someday. i don\u0026rsquo;t think i\u0026rsquo;ll ever see carl again. but i saw him. we saw each other. we found each other in the cosmos, and that was wonderful.\n","title":""},{"date":"2021-01-24","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/210124_barbara-tuchman_books-carry-civilization-forward/","summary":"“Books are the carriers of civilization. Without books, history is silent, literature dumb, science crippled, thought and speculation at a standstill. Without books, the development of civilization would have been impossible. They are engines of change (as the poet said), windows on the world and lighthouses erected in the sea of time. They are companions, teachers, magicians, bankers of the treasures of the mind. Books are humanity in print.\u0026quot;","tags":[],"text":"“books are the carriers of civilization. without books, history is silent, literature dumb, science crippled, thought and speculation at a standstill. without books, the development of civilization would have been impossible. they are engines of change (as the poet said), windows on the world and lighthouses erected in the sea of time. they are companions, teachers, magicians, bankers of the treasures of the mind. books are humanity in print.\u0026quot;\n","title":""},{"date":"2020-02-29","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/200229_stendhal_belleza-promesa-felicidad/","summary":"La belleza es promesa de felicidad.","tags":[],"text":"la belleza es promesa de felicidad.\n","title":""},{"date":"2018-01-03","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/180103_jonwayne_i-need-to-slow/","summary":"I need to slow down, but I need a good friend to come and tell me how.","tags":[],"text":"i need to slow down, but i need a good friend to come and tell me how.\n","title":""},{"date":"2014-09-18","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/140918_jim-ignatowski_bueno-television-algo-importante/","summary":"Lo bueno de la television es que si algo importante ocurre en cualquier parte del mundo, sea de dia o por la noche, siempre puedes cambiar de canal.","tags":[],"text":"lo bueno de la television es que si algo importante ocurre en cualquier parte del mundo, sea de dia o por la noche, siempre puedes cambiar de canal.\n","title":""},{"date":"2013-12-20","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/131220_ambrose-bierce_war-is-geography-for/","summary":"War is God´s way of teaching American´s geography","tags":[],"text":"war is god´s way of teaching american´s geography\n","title":""},{"date":"2026-03-13","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/260313_fran-lebowitz_no-one-can-afford/","summary":"No one can afford to live in New York. Yet, eight million people do.","tags":[],"text":"no one can afford to live in new york. yet, eight million people do.\n","title":""},{"date":"2023-02-08","image":"","imageAlt":"","link":"http://192.168.178.34:1313/quotes/230208_greg-mckeow_can-two-things-simultaneously/","summary":"We can do two things simultaneously—but we can\u0026rsquo;t concentrate on two things simultaneously","tags":[],"text":"we can do two things s